WEBVTT

00:01.440 --> 00:02.774
- I wanna go legit.
- You can't.

00:02.842 --> 00:04.676
Then I get Lola Jensen
to hack into the bar

00:04.713 --> 00:06.781
and just put me in there
just like she did with Harvard.

00:06.832 --> 00:08.366
Rule number one
of not getting caught,

00:08.451 --> 00:09.918
you don't move
the goddamn body.

00:09.985 --> 00:11.818
Harvey, I'm stuck.

00:11.871 --> 00:14.088
I can't live my whole life
like this.

00:14.156 --> 00:15.457
We're investment bankers.

00:15.508 --> 00:17.658
Our job blows yours
out of the water.

00:17.710 --> 00:18.927
Just admit it,
you want me to take the job,

00:18.994 --> 00:20.178
but you're too afraid
to say it.

00:20.262 --> 00:21.829
I want you to take the job.

00:21.881 --> 00:24.165
You and your associate
conspired with Harold Gunderson

00:24.216 --> 00:26.217
to file a lawsuit
against your own clients.

00:26.302 --> 00:27.635
That is a bribe.

00:27.686 --> 00:29.053
Quelling knows
about your bullshit lawsuit

00:29.138 --> 00:30.054
with Harold Gunderson.

00:30.139 --> 00:31.639
You need to call
Lola Jensen.

00:31.690 --> 00:33.358
You said it yourself,
hacking into the bar

00:33.442 --> 00:35.109
is twice the crime
I've been committing.

00:35.177 --> 00:37.312
I am telling you
Quelling is on the trail,

00:37.363 --> 00:39.113
and you quitting
isn't gonna change that.

00:39.181 --> 00:40.315
You're letting Mike
walk out the door

00:40.366 --> 00:41.449
without trying to stop him,

00:41.517 --> 00:42.784
and anytime I ask you
about anything

00:42.851 --> 00:45.737
all you say is,
"I can't talk about it."

00:45.821 --> 00:47.355
Mike is gone, Harvey.

00:47.406 --> 00:48.523
The jeopardy's gone too.

00:48.574 --> 00:49.824
And now you wanna tell someone

00:49.875 --> 00:52.126
who keeps finding a reason
to be pissed at you,

00:52.194 --> 00:54.128
and it's not the third time,
and it's not the fifth time,

00:54.196 --> 00:55.547
and it's not the last time.

00:55.631 --> 00:57.131
You took money
from our client's competitors

00:57.199 --> 00:58.866
to trump up
your bullshit suit.

00:58.918 --> 01:00.201
The penalty
is being disbarred.

01:00.252 --> 01:02.554
Being a lawyer
is what I am.

01:02.638 --> 01:04.138
And if you take that away--

01:04.206 --> 01:05.138
It's up to you.

01:05.206 --> 01:06.841
I'll drop the suit.

01:06.892 --> 01:09.344
I'm officially a member
of the New York bar.

01:09.395 --> 01:10.711
You went to Lola?

01:10.763 --> 01:13.515
I want to stay.

01:20.489 --> 01:21.573
I'd bring in champagne,

01:21.657 --> 01:22.907
but after
all we've been through,

01:22.992 --> 01:25.443
I think scotch
seems more appropriate.

01:25.528 --> 01:27.445
Does it?

01:29.448 --> 01:31.749
Harvey, we've had
this conversation once.

01:31.834 --> 01:33.501
If you want someone
who doesn't speak their mind,

01:33.569 --> 01:35.670
I'm not that person.

01:35.737 --> 01:36.921
I know.

01:37.006 --> 01:40.041
And Mike staying
doesn't change my opinion.

01:40.092 --> 01:42.877
Telling Scottie about him
is a mistake.

01:42.928 --> 01:45.630
I know.

01:45.714 --> 01:47.081
Then why are you
being so quiet?

01:47.132 --> 01:49.634
Someone who keeps finding
a way to be pissed at me,

01:49.718 --> 01:51.636
and it's not the third time
or the fifth time

01:51.720 --> 01:53.021
or the last time.

01:53.088 --> 01:55.440
- I wasn't gonna say that.
- Yeah, well, you did.

01:55.524 --> 01:57.108
Because you forced it
out of me.

01:57.192 --> 02:02.063
Donna, do you want me
and Scottie to succeed or not?

02:02.114 --> 02:04.065
I want you to be happy.

02:04.116 --> 02:06.117
- That's an evasive answer.
- No, it isn't.

02:06.201 --> 02:09.070
Just isn't up to me
to decide what that means.

02:11.907 --> 02:15.493
Now are we gonna drink
to Mike staying or what?

02:15.578 --> 02:17.912
Give me that.

02:17.963 --> 02:19.998
Not that one.

02:20.082 --> 02:21.082
The bigger one.

02:21.133 --> 02:22.283
Seriously?

02:22.334 --> 02:24.785
[Glasses clink]

02:26.000 --> 02:32.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:36.515 --> 02:37.965
- Hey.
- Hey.

02:38.017 --> 02:39.467
I'm so glad you're home.

02:39.518 --> 02:41.653
I made dinner
because I want to celebrate.

02:41.737 --> 02:45.273
I'm not taking the job.

02:45.324 --> 02:46.357
What?

02:46.442 --> 02:48.109
I went to see Harvey,

02:48.160 --> 02:50.311
and, um...

02:50.362 --> 02:52.413
I told him that I'm staying.

02:54.116 --> 02:58.252
What about the fact
that it was eating you up?

02:58.320 --> 03:00.321
Look, Rachel, I know
this isn't what you wanted.

03:00.372 --> 03:01.489
What I wanted?

03:01.540 --> 03:03.341
I didn't wanna give you
my opinion at all,

03:03.425 --> 03:04.709
but you forced it out of me,

03:04.793 --> 03:06.878
and then you told me that you
were gonna take the job.

03:06.962 --> 03:07.962
Okay, Rachel--

03:08.013 --> 03:09.213
No, and now
you come in here,

03:09.298 --> 03:10.598
and you tell me
you're gonna stay a fraud.

03:10.666 --> 03:12.350
- A lawyer.
- A fraud.

03:16.021 --> 03:17.772
What happened
to accepting me for who I am?

03:17.839 --> 03:20.475
What happened
to you taking the job?

03:22.945 --> 03:26.447
It was a way out.

03:26.515 --> 03:28.533
You said you were afraid
if you told me your opinion,

03:28.617 --> 03:30.234
I'd hold it against you,

03:30.319 --> 03:34.072
but now that I'm not doing
what you told me to,

03:34.156 --> 03:35.289
you're holding it
against me.

03:35.357 --> 03:36.290
I am.

03:36.358 --> 03:37.709
Yeah, that's not fair.

03:37.793 --> 03:39.577
I wanna know what changed

03:39.662 --> 03:41.529
from when you told me you were
gonna take the job to now.

03:41.580 --> 03:43.864
I went to see Quelling.

03:43.916 --> 03:45.049
He once had
an offer on the table

03:45.134 --> 03:47.135
that would change his life,

03:47.202 --> 03:48.469
and he turned it down

03:48.537 --> 03:51.472
because he wanted to do
what was right for his clients.

03:51.540 --> 03:53.808
Cost him everything.

03:53.875 --> 03:55.426
The only thing
it didn't cost him

03:55.511 --> 03:57.378
was his ability
to practice law.

03:57.429 --> 03:58.980
And I didn't want
to take it away from him

03:59.047 --> 04:00.047
just like I don't wanna
take it away from me.

04:00.099 --> 04:01.099
Mike.

04:01.183 --> 04:04.268
You said that staying
is eating me up,

04:04.353 --> 04:07.155
but the thought of going
is eating me up more.

04:09.024 --> 04:12.527
I'm just--I'm not ready
to leave, Rachel.

04:17.281 --> 04:20.233
Thanks.

04:20.285 --> 04:21.836
Michael Ross.

04:21.903 --> 04:23.004
Yes?

04:23.071 --> 04:25.673
We'd like to ask you
a few questions.

04:25.741 --> 04:26.791
Who's "we"?

04:26.875 --> 04:30.044
The U.S. attorney's office.

04:31.130 --> 04:32.463
What can I help you with?

04:32.548 --> 04:36.801
We'd prefer to have
this conversation in private.

04:38.920 --> 04:41.889
- Prefer?
- Insist.

04:50.315 --> 04:53.067
Scottie.

04:54.453 --> 04:55.820
I know we got in a fight,

04:55.904 --> 04:58.990
but drinking before 10:00 a.m.,
is that really the answer?

05:01.109 --> 05:02.276
It is on <i>Mad Men.</i>

05:02.327 --> 05:05.780
Who's that guy
think he is anyway?

05:07.166 --> 05:09.116
Mike's staying.

05:10.586 --> 05:11.753
You must be happy.

05:11.804 --> 05:13.454
I am.

05:13.505 --> 05:18.059
Scottie, I'm gonna do better
about being open with you.

05:19.461 --> 05:21.462
Good.

05:21.513 --> 05:25.149
Are we good?

05:25.234 --> 05:26.467
We're good.

05:26.518 --> 05:28.519
Then let's go out tonight
and have some fun.

05:28.604 --> 05:30.855
I'm in.

05:36.111 --> 05:39.580
Scottie.

05:39.648 --> 05:40.665
Yeah?

05:43.652 --> 05:45.586
Let's go somewhere new.

05:49.508 --> 05:51.459
Donna, I don't wanna hear it.

05:51.510 --> 05:52.627
I didn't tell her
about Mike.

05:52.678 --> 05:54.095
Harvey, Stephanie Liston
just called me.

05:54.162 --> 05:57.331
Your friend
from the U.S. Attorney's office?

05:57.382 --> 06:00.000
She said they just brought
Mike in for questioning.

06:03.806 --> 06:05.973
Mr. Ross, Eric Woodall.

06:06.024 --> 06:07.475
I'm the U.S. attorney--

06:07.526 --> 06:08.810
For the Southern district
of New York.

06:08.861 --> 06:10.228
Yeah, I know who you are.

06:10.312 --> 06:13.030
Then you know
you're in a shitload of trouble.

06:13.115 --> 06:16.367
You wanna come clean,
or should I lay it out for you?

06:16.485 --> 06:18.091
I don't know
what you're talking about.

06:18.370 --> 06:20.071
You conspired
with Harold Gunderson,

06:20.155 --> 06:21.989
to defraud
the United States government

06:22.040 --> 06:25.793
by paying off witnesses
against Ava Hessington.

06:25.861 --> 06:28.129
[Chuckles]
What?

06:28.196 --> 06:30.131
You sound surprised.

06:30.198 --> 06:31.749
I am
because it's bullshit.

06:31.834 --> 06:33.718
It's not bullshit.

06:33.802 --> 06:36.220
You're facing some major
prison time, my friend.

06:36.305 --> 06:37.922
- I'm not your friend.
- You can be.

06:38.006 --> 06:39.423
Pass.

06:39.508 --> 06:41.893
I settled a lawsuit, okay?
I didn't do anything wrong.

06:41.977 --> 06:44.478
Hey, I don't think you did.

06:44.546 --> 06:46.731
Well, not on your own anyway.

06:46.815 --> 06:49.216
Is there a question?

06:49.268 --> 06:50.384
Come on,
you're a bright young man.

06:50.435 --> 06:52.386
You see where I'm going.

06:52.437 --> 06:55.156
I don't want the dealer.

06:55.223 --> 06:57.074
I want the supplier.

06:57.159 --> 06:59.026
Harvey Specter.

06:59.077 --> 07:03.781
Roll over on him,
I'll cut a deal right now.

07:06.535 --> 07:10.237
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

07:10.289 --> 07:13.507
♪ get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

07:13.575 --> 07:16.627
♪ everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

07:16.712 --> 07:20.381
♪ everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

07:20.432 --> 07:23.384
♪ Living in a beehive
of your mind ♪

